\f0\b 3.1 What Was Changed
\f1\b0 \
\

\fs22 A complete coworking and sharing system was implemented, allowing users to share individual transcripts or entire folders with other users at different permission levels (view or edit).
\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.1 Backend: Access Control System (
\f2\b0\fs20 server/checkAccess.ts
\f0\b\fs22 )
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 A centralized access control function 
\f2\fs20 checkAccess(userId, resourceType, resourceId)
\f1\fs22  was created. It checks:
\f2\fs18 \uc0\u8232 1. Is the user the owner of the resource? -> Full access\u8232 2. Does a share record exist granting this user access? -> Permission-based access\u8232 3. For transcripts in a shared folder: does a folder-level share exist? -> Inherited access\u8232 \u8232 Returns: \{ allowed: boolean, permission: 'owner' | 'edit' | 'view' | null \}
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.2 Backend: Share Routes (
\f2\b0\fs20 server/routes/shares.ts
\f0\b\fs22 , 401 lines)
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 A full REST API for sharing:
\f2\fs18 \uc0\u8232 POST   /api/shares              Create a share (email, resourceType, resourceId, permission)\u8232 GET    /api/shares/by-resource   List shares for a specific resource\u8232 GET    /api/shares/shared-with-me  List all resources shared with the current user\u8232 PATCH  /api/shares/:id            Update share permission\u8232 DELETE /api/shares/:id            Revoke a share (soft delete via revoked_at)\u8232 \u8232 Security features:\u8232 - Only the resource owner can create/modify/revoke shares\u8232 - Email-based sharing: if the target email doesn't have an account, the share\u8232   silently succeeds (no information disclosure about user existence)\u8232 - Self-sharing is rejected\u8232 - Duplicate shares are detected and updated rather than duplicated\u8232 - Revoked shares can be re-activated with a new permission level
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.3 Backend: Transcript Route Security Hardening
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 The 
\f2\fs20 server/routes/transcripts.ts
\f1\fs22  file was significantly modified (~148 line changes) to integrate access control checks into every endpoint:
\f2\fs18 \uc0\u8232 - GET /api/transcripts/:id       Now checks checkAccess() before returning data\u8232 - PUT /api/transcripts/:id       Only allows edits if permission is 'owner' or 'edit'\u8232 - DELETE /api/transcripts/:id    Only allows deletion by owner\u8232 - PUT /api/transcripts/:id/segments  Edit-permission required for segment saves\u8232 - Annotation routes: access-controlled
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.4 Frontend: ShareModal Component (
\f2\b0\fs20 src/components/sharing/ShareModal.tsx
\f0\b\fs22 , 180 lines)
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 A modal dialog for managing shares:
\f2\fs18 \uc0\u8232 - Email input to share with a user\u8232 - Permission dropdown (View / Edit)\u8232 - List of current shares with permission badges\u8232 - Revoke button for each share\u8232 - Integrated into TranscriptToolbar via a "Share" button
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.5 Frontend: Shared Context & Sidebar
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 A 
\f2\fs20 SharedContext
\f1\fs22  (
\f2\fs20 src/contexts/SharedContext.tsx
\f1\fs22 ) provides a 
\f2\fs20 useShared()
\f1\fs22  hook that fetches and caches 
\f2\fs20 /api/shares/shared-with-me
\f1\fs22 . The sidebar (
\f2\fs20 Sidebar.tsx
\f1\fs22 ) was modified to show a "Shared with Me" section listing transcripts and folders shared by other users, with visual indicators for permission level (view/edit badge).
\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.6 Frontend: Permission-Aware UI
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 Multiple components were updated to respect permissions:
\f2\fs18 \uc0\u8232 - TranscriptToolbar: Share button visible only to owners\u8232 - TranscriptText: Edit controls hidden for view-only users\u8232 - MetadataEditor: Read-only mode for view-only users\u8232 - TranscriptViewerPage: Permission state threaded through all child components
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 3.1.7 Auto-Save for Notes and Bookmarks
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 Notes and bookmarks are now automatically saved when the user modifies them, instead of requiring a manual save action. This was implemented alongside the sharing feature to ensure shared collaborators see real-time updates.
\fs24 \
\

