\f0\b\fs22 4.1.2 Media Playback Diagnostic Logging (c3f9791, c5bab60)
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 Added extensive console logging throughout the media playback pipeline to debug issues where audio/video wouldn't play in the browser:
\f2\fs18 \uc0\u8232 - useAudioPlayer.ts: Logs audio element creation, source URL, load events,\u8232   play/pause state changes, error events with error codes, and duration detection\u8232 - TranscriptViewerPage.tsx: Logs media URL resolution, file type detection,\u8232   and player initialization\u8232 - Server: Added media-type-aware response headers for audio streaming
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 4.1.3 Automatic Browser-Playable Audio Conversion (12f1738)
\f1\b0\fs24 \

\fs22 Added a 
\f2\fs20 convertToBrowserPlayable()
\f1\fs22  function to the transcription pipeline in 
\f2\fs20 server/transcription.ts
\f1\fs22 :
\fs24 \
\

\f2\fs18 BROWSER_PLAYABLE_FORMATS = ['.mp3', '.wav', '.ogg', '.m4a', '.aac', '.flac', '.webm', '.mp4', '.oga']\uc0\u8232 \u8232 If the source file is NOT in a browser-playable format:\u8232 1. Convert to MP3 at 44.1kHz stereo 128kbps via ffmpeg\u8232 2. Upload the MP3 to S3 with the same key but .mp3 extension\u8232 3. Update the transcript's file_url in the database to point to the MP3\u8232 \u8232 If the source file IS browser-playable: no conversion (return null)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\fs22 This ensures that all transcripts have browser-playable audio URLs regardless of the original upload format. The conversion runs at the beginning of the pipeline, before Whisper processing, and is non-fatal (errors are caught and logged).
\fs24 \
\

\fs22 A 
\f2\fs20 /api/media/:key(*)
\f1\fs22  endpoint was also added to 
\f2\fs20 server/index.ts
\f1\fs22  to proxy S3 media files to the browser with appropriate content-type headers (54 line change). This allows the frontend audio player to stream audio directly from the server without CORS issues from S3.
