\f0\b 8.1 Architecture
\f1\b0 \
\

\fs22 This feature converts the presentation mode from a full-page navigation (leaving the transcript viewer) to a synced pop-out window (opens a new browser window while the main app stays open). The main app owns all audio/video playback and broadcasts state to the pop-out window via the BroadcastChannel API.
\fs24 \
\

\f0\b\fs22 8.1.1 BroadcastChannel Sync Hook (
\f2\b0\fs20 src/hooks/usePresentSync.ts
\f0\b\fs22 )
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\

\fs22 Two hooks for cross-window communication:
\fs24 \
\

\f2\fs18 usePresentBroadcaster(transcriptId)
\f0\b\fs20  \'97sed by the main app:
\f2\b0\fs18 \uc0\u8232 - Opens a BroadcastChannel named 'mms-present-sync'\u8232 - broadcast(state): sends current playback state to all listeners\u8232 - onCommand(handler): registers a handler for commands from the pop-out\u8232 - Responds to 'request_state' handshake from pop-out on mount\u8232 \u8232 State broadcast payload (PresentState):\u8232   transcriptId, currentTime, isPlaying, playbackRate, duration,\u8232   filename, mediaType, mediaUrl, segments[]
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f2\fs18 usePresentReceiver(transcriptId)
\f0\b\fs20  \'97sed by the pop-out window:
