\f0\b 9.1 What Was Changed
\f1\b0 \
\

\fs22 Added 
\f2\fs20 speech_model: 'universal-3-pro'
\f1\fs22  to the AssemblyAI transcription configuration object.
\fs24 \
\

\f2\fs18 // Before:\uc0\u8232 const config: any = \{\u8232   audio_url: uploadUrl,\u8232   speaker_labels: true,\u8232   sentiment_analysis: true,\u8232   ...\u8232 \};\u8232 \u8232 // After:\u8232 const config: any = \{\u8232   audio_url: uploadUrl,\u8232   speech_model: 'universal-3-pro',\u8232   speaker_labels: true,\u8232   sentiment_analysis: true,\u8232   ...\u8232 \};
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\b 9.2 Why
\f1\b0 \
\

\fs22 The AssemblyAI API began requiring an explicit 
\f2\fs20 speech_model
\f1\fs22  value. Without it, the API returned the validation error 
\f4\i "speech_models" must be a non-empty list
\f1\i0 , causing diarization to fail for every transcription. This meant no speaker identification, no enriched data (word-level confidence, sentiment, entities), and the Claude enriched refinement path was unavailable \'97orcing the pipeline to use the inferior standard refinement path with heuristic speaker assignment.
\fs24 \
\
